              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><b>sillinor7</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/29/2004&nbsp;: 10:18:11 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Its easier than you think and it can be done.  The only place I've done it well is by the SE basement.  Head towards SE basement and go past the 3 wrulons but stop before you go down the stairs heading to the basement, turn around.  You will notice 2 sides.  On each side there are 2 Valorous Guards, a small set of steps, and another Guard.  Right out front there are the 3 wrulons.  You can aggro kite them all and I ussually keep around six at once killed but if you have BOT you can keep 7 at once killed.  <br /><br />Buffs<img src="images/icon_smile_blush.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br /><br /><br />Shield of Maelin<br />Sow(have potions)<br />Seduction of Saryn-must have<br />Force Shield-strongly recommended<br />Virtue-must have this or at least POT9,temp, Brell's some good HP buffs unless you have 3k or so HP's unbuffed then you should be good<br /><br />Spell Lineup<img src="images/icon_smile_clown.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br />Vexing Mordina or Saryn's Kiss<br />embracing darkness-must have <br />BOT(if you have if not use Funeral Pyre)<br />Pyrocrour<br />Dark Plague<br />Shackle of Spirit(for the Valourous Guards if you want)<br />Comatose(Death Peace works well too)<br /><br />Highly Recommended<img src="images/icon_smile_tongue.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br />Ceramic Skull of Decay-if you don't have one grab a Naki's ring in bazaar it's summoned and ussually costs about 15 plat.. YOU MUST HAVE SPELL HASTE<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />PICK A SIDE!! stick to one side.  All you have to do is pull the Valorous Guard closest to the wall(should be a single).  I stand as far away as I can so I can get an FD off if it resists.  If you have pet hold AA that is useful as well.  Stay as close you can to the wall and on the darker part of the marble floor.  Run it from the wall around the column there and then back around to the column by the stairs leading to the basement and around that.  As long as you don't step out past the first set of tiles the other Valorous Guards should not argo you.  When you first start out doing this it can be a bit tricky so I recommend slowing after you snare just until you become a pro at it.  Also, if darkness wears off you can FD and pet can handle tanking it for awhile then you can pop up and snare again.<br /><br />Kite the one Valouros. After that you pull the other by the median(on your side).  You will have to split this time so FD-send pet or snare and then FD split.. up to you.  Kill the 2nd valorous and then the 3rd one on your side right up the steps.  You don't have to worry about the other one argo'ing because of the median between them.  Once you're done killing all 3 valorous then go and FD split the 3 wrulons.  On your way back just make sure you pull the Wrulons to the side you've already wiped so they don't argo anything else and don't get too close to any of the 3 Valorous's left.<br /><br />If you have the timing of the camp down you should have a nice big space to aggro kite the Wrulons in.  Run them from the wall to the steps and back again.  I DON'T run around the columns when kiting the Wrulons because they will get caught up and a pathing bug causes them to fall in odd places.  You have plenty of room so with a spell haste just use it.  The cool thing is they run at 12 percent so you're good after that.  It's important to have the 3 Valorous on that side killed so they don't pop when you are killing the Wrulon.  If they do just FD and take pet loss.  If you see them pop just root/rot the Wrulon and finish it off.  If you can keep a room of 6 Valorian Guards killed in the basement you should have no trouble doing this with a little practice. If you can't do that then just kill the 3 Valorous Guards and then 1 or 2 Wrulons by kiting.  Actually, doing that is a good idea at first until you get used to it.<br /><br />I have got longblades of Vitality here, etheral and specs, Wrulon eye, Band of the risen, cape of the proud, defender's lightblade, and another really sweet range item.  This stuff sells really great<br /><br />I am on Prexus server so if this confused you and you'd like me to show you send me a tell.  Also, as far as I know it can only be done by the SE basement where the Valorous Guards can all be snared and don't summon. The Wrulon protectors,guards, and sentries all do not summon and can be snared.  Do NOT FUCK with the rabid Wrulon I cannot stress this enough.  <br /><br /><br />IMPORTANT <img src="images/icon_smile_sad.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /><br />Out front you will see a roamer named LT just look for him when you pull the wrulons.  This is why you have to pull the wrulons down the small set of steps and aggro kite in that area and why the Valorous guards must be killed to get the Wrulons. <br /><br />EDIT:  Moved to Guides section. (TPO)</span></font></td>
